make sure you have autoreconf installed (xutils-dev + aptdh-autoreconf and autotools-dev)
I have found that the best way to install i3-gaps on debian is with i3-gaps-deb


How to pack and install a program from source
./configurationScript
make
sudo checkinstall

if you build without checkinstall, remember to link your new libs if there's any to the lib database (especially if the package manager doesn't do it for you.
<command>

Tip: if on compile time the compiler tells you you're missing a lib.h, it's most likely that the header file is in the *-dev version of the lib's package, not the main one.


